to her godmother and mother respectively.  The next four were all "made
up stories about real people."  Tommy, Ann, Sonny and Donell are all
Tammy's relatives.  Sonny and Donell are Tammy's brothers.  The last
three stories, HOLLY< MR.LEWIS and MISS.HIRSH are about a classmate,
and about Tammy's regular sixth grade teachers.

Beginning with the very first class, Tammy had shown an interest in
"communicating" with the computer, and in using the computer as a
typewriter.  In the second and third classes I showed Tammy how to
write procedures using the PRINT command, first with brackets, then
with a variable input.  Her typing difficulties made it hard for her to
be successful using the PRINT command.

I created a special program for Tammy called LETTER, which allowed her
to choose a name for a letter, then type whatever she wants to write
directly into the computer.  The LETTER procedure interprets each of
Tammy's typed lines as a separate "REQUEST" and automatically makes a
procedure to print out her lines in order.  If Tammy wants to change a
line she can use the rubout key, before she types a carriage
return.  Other than that, it has no special editing capability.  When
Tammy finishes with a story, she types END, which causes the LETTER
procedure to finish defining the procedure.  It then types, out "HERE
